Admissions from 2004 until 2009  Married in the summer of 2005  John and his wife Lauren became very actively engaged in ministry to the Corps of Cadets  extending spiritual care and mentoring to a number of cadets  During this time  Chaplain Casper also served as an Assistant Investigator for the Inspector General s Office  coached VMI s Ceremonial Drill Team  served as a tactical officer in barracks  helped to lead the Character Counts program in the local Lexington school system  and were foster parents in the Rockbridge area  In July of 2009  Chaplain Casper left the Institute to attend seminary at Regent University s School of Divinity in Virginia Beach  While in seminary  John was also engaged in full time ministry as the Youth and Young Adult Pastor in a local non denominational Bible church  During their time in Virginia Beach  John and Lauren obediently followed God s leading on two separate occasions  adopting two children from Ethiopia  In early January of 2014  Chaplain Casper was selected as the Institute s first Associate Chaplain to the Corps of Cadets  John has earned an B A  in English from VMI  as well as a M A  in Theology  emphasis in Ministerial Leadership  and a M Ed  in Christian Education  emphasis in Character Education  from Regent University in Virginia Beach  VA  John and Lauren live in Lexington  VA and have two beautiful children  a son  Mareto  and a daughter  Arsema    Related Information Chaplain s Office Chaplain James Park Assoc  Chaplain John Casper  04   50th Anniversary of Ministry to the Corps Mary Cannon Secretary to the Chaplain Old Hospital Virginia Military Institute Lexington  VA  24450 P   540  464 7390 F   540  464 7727 VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an educatio